What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Power Sports After Market?

Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Power Sports After Market

The power sports after market is expected to witness market growth at a rate of 5.60% in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028 and is expected to reach USD 15,946.55 million by 2028. Data Bridge Market Research report on power sports after market provides analysis and insights regarding the various factors expected to be prevalent throughout the forecast period while providing their impacts on the market’s growth. The rise in the emphasis on improving the driving experience of power sports vehicles is escalating the growth of power sports after market.

The after market refers to the auto industry’s after-sale market. It includes vehicle parts, collision repair and accessories, equipment, replacement tires, service repair, sold after the sale of the original vehicle. The companies included in the after market are manufacturing, re-manufacturing, distribution, automotive accessories, retailing, and installation of replacement vehicle parts, service repair and equipment.

The rise in number of off-road events accelerating the demand for power sports vehicles acts as one of the major factors driving the growth of power sports after market. The increase in the accidents and off-road racing causing damages to vehicle parts, and high demand for the after market because of its cost-effective after market products accelerate the power sports after market growth. The increase in development and integration of new components, such as audio bars and communication systems and availability of low-cost parts and components compared to products offered by the OEMs further influence the power sports after market. Additionally, high participation in off-roading and recreational activities, increase in demand for vehicles, expansion of e-commerce platforms and surge in disposable income positively affect the power sports after market. Furthermore, the surge in investments by power sports vehicle manufacturers and government authorities in order to develop off-roading infrastructure extend profitable opportunities to the power sports after market players in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028.

On the other hand, high initial investments required for setting up manufacturing facilities for after market parts are expected to obstruct the power sports after market growth. The negative impact of COVID-19 is projected to challenge the power sports after market.

